-- Apranga Clothing Sales Jumped 26% in Year to a Record in August
-- B y   M i l d a   S e p u t y t e
-- 2012-09-03T07:55:02Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-09-03/apranga-clothing-sales-jumped-26-in-year-to-a-record-in-august.html
Apranga AB, the biggest Baltic
clothing retailer, said sales grew 26 percent in August from the
same period last year, the highest one-month revenue on record.  Sales grew to 55.2 million litai ($20.1 million), the
Vilnius-based company said in a statement to the stock exchange
today. Revenue grew 25 percent from last year in the January-
August period, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Milda Seputyte in Vilnius at 
